quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  40,67,"It is He who created you of dust then of a sperm-drop, then of a blood-clot, then He delivers you as infants, then that you may come of age, then that you may be old men -- though some of you there are who die before it -- and that you may reach a stated term; haply you will understand"
  40,68,"It is He who gives life, and makes to die; and when He decrees a thing, He but says to it 'Be,' and it is"
  40,69,"Hast thou not regarded those who dispute concerning the signs of God, how they are turned about"
  40,70,Those who cry lies to the Book and that wherewith We sent Our Messengers -- soon they will know
  40,71,"When the fetters and chains are on their necks, and they dragged"
  40,72,"into the boiling water, then into the Fire they are poured"
  40,73,"then it is said to them, 'Where are those you associated, apart from God"
  40,74,"They shall say, 'They have gone astray from us; nay, but it was nothing at all that we called upon aforetime.' Even so God leads astray the unbelievers"
  40,75,"That is because you rejoiced in the earth without right, and were exultant"
  40,76,"Enter the gates of Gehenna, to dwell therein forever.' How evil is the lodging of those that are proud"
  40,77,"So be thou patient; surely God's promise is true. Whether We show thee a part of that We promise them, or We call thee unto Us, to Us they shall be returned"